return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527544\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fjy1665702564615.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fjy1665702564615.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fjy1665702564615.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fjy1665702564615\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Adding, Copying, Moving, and Replacing Struct Members \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__addingcopyingmovingand_replacing_struct_members_61317\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can add and replace members in existing Structs, insert them at specified positions, detach them, or move them to new positions, or to new Structs.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18149e1_d18150e1_d18151e1\">Assume that the variables <code class=\"ph codeph\">vStructA</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">vStructB</code> refer to the following Structs, respectively:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_d18152e1_d18153e1_d18154e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>StructA (Insects) and StructB (Fishes)</figcaption>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_w3341ab1b5b5b3b1_w3342ab1b5b5b3_w3343ab1b5b5_w3344ab1b5_w3345ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Structs A (a=ant, b=bee, a=aphid, b=butterfly, c=cockroach); Struct B (a=angelfish, c=catfish, a=anemonefish, c=clownfish, d=dragonfish)\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" height=\"742\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"1438\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__topic_d12982e1_d12983e1_d12984e1_d12985e1_d12986e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059459e80\">\n                        \n Adding a Member to a Struct\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18158e1_d18159e1_d18160e1\">If a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">struct</span> variable refers to an empty Struct, you can add a new member by specifying the new member name after the de-reference operator and assigning it a value. If the member does not yet exist, it is added. For example, to create Struct A, you can start with creating an empty Struct and adding a member:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA = $newstruct\nvStructA-&gt;a = \"ant\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18161e1_d18162e1_d18163e1\">If a Struct has one member, you can append a named Struct member by specifying -1 as the index position. For example</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;a{-1} = \"aphid\"\nvStructB-&gt;a{-1} = \"angelfish\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18164e1_d18165e1_d18166e1\">This implicitly inserts a new member named <code class=\"ph codeph\">a</code> after the last member named <code class=\"ph codeph\">a</code>, or as the last member if there was no <code class=\"ph codeph\">a</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__topic_d12987e1_d12988e1_d12989e1_d12990e1_d12991e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059459e114\">\n                        \n Copying and Replacing Struct Members\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18170e1_d18171e1_d18172e1\">The following code copies members of Struct B to Struct A.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;b = vStructB-&gt;c</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18173e1_d18174e1_d18175e1\">Assignment is by value, so the existing values for the StructA members are replaced by the values specified in the right side of the assignment. If no other <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">struct</span> variables point to these members, they are deleted.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18176e1_d18177e1_d18178e1\">The new values are inserted in at the point where the first <code class=\"ph codeph\">b</code> member was located.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_d18179e1_d18180e1_d18181e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Struct A with New Values for Members named b</figcaption>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_w3346ab1b5b9c11b3b1_w3347ab1b5b9c11b3_w3348ab1b5b9c11_w3349ab1b5b9_w3350ab1b5_w3351ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Struct A (a=ant, b=catfish, b=clownfish, a=aphid, c=cockroach)\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb_copytomember.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" height=\"577\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb_copytomember.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"522\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__topic_d12992e1_d12993e1_d12994e1_d12995e1_d12996e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059459e158\">\n                        \n Replacing and Appending Struct Members by Name and Index\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18185e1_d18186e1_d18187e1\">When using the Struct index operator after a member name, only the member at that index position is changed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18188e1_d18189e1_d18190e1\">Variables <code class=\"ph codeph\">vStructA</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">vStructB</code> refer to the original contents of the Structs illustrated\n            in <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#fjy1665702564615__fig_d18152e1_d18153e1_d18154e1\">Figure 1</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18191e1_d18192e1_d18193e1\">The following code accesses the members of Struct 1 by both name and index and changes its contents.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fjy1665702564615_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__codeblock_ath_yhc_5cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;a{2} = vStructB-&gt;c  [<strong class=\"ph b\">1</strong>]\nvStructA-&gt;b{-1} = vStructB-&gt;a [<strong class=\"ph b\">2</strong>]</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8498e1_d8499e1_d8500e1\">Replaces the second member named <code class=\"ph codeph\">a</code>\n               in StructA (<code class=\"ph codeph\">aphid</code>) with the values of the members named\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">c</code> in StructB (<code class=\"ph codeph\">catfish</code> and\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">clownfish</code>). </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8501e1_d8502e1_d8503e1\">Copies the values of members named\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">a</code> in StructB (<code class=\"ph codeph\">anglefish</code> and\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">anemonefish</code>) after the last member named <code class=\"ph codeph\">b</code> in\n               StructA (<code class=\"ph codeph\">butterfly</code>). </li>\n</ol>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_d18197e1_d18198e1_d18199e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 3. </span>Struct A After Replacing Contents by Name and Index</figcaption>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_w3362ab1b5c11c13b3b1_w3363ab1b5c11c13b3_w3364ab1b5c11c13_w3365ab1b5c11_w3366ab1b5_w3367ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Struct A After Replacing Contents by Name and Index\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb_replaceybynameindex.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" height=\"877\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb_replaceybynameindex.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"522\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__topic_d12997e1_d12998e1_d12999e1_d13000e1_d13001e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059459e250\">\n                        \n Copying and Replacing Struct Members by Index Only\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18203e1_d18204e1_d18205e1\">You can also add Struct members at a specific index position in the list of members using the wildcard to specify a collection and the index operator to specify a position in the collection (that is, the list of members).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18206e1_d18207e1_d18208e1\">Variables <code class=\"ph codeph\">vStructA</code> and\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">vStructB</code> refer to the original contents of the Structs illustrated\n            in <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#fjy1665702564615__fig_d18152e1_d18153e1_d18154e1\">Figure 1</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104fjy1665702564615_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__codeblock_v4f_p3c_5cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;*{4} = vStructB-&gt;c [<strong class=\"ph b\">1</strong>]\nvStructA-&gt;*{-1} = vStructB-&gt;a{2} [<strong class=\"ph b\">2</strong>]</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8504e1_d8505e1_d8506e1\">Replaces the fourth member in StructA\n                  (<code class=\"ph codeph\">butterfly</code>) with the values of the members named\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">c</code> in StructB (<code class=\"ph codeph\">catfish</code> and\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">clownfish</code>). </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8507e1_d8508e1_d8509e1\">Copies the values of second members named <code class=\"ph codeph\">a</code> from StructB (<code class=\"ph codeph\">anemonefish</code>) after the last member in StructA.\n </li>\n</ol>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_d18212e1_d18213e1_d18214e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 4. </span>Struct A After Replacing Contents at Index</figcaption>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__fig_w3378ab1b5c13c11b3b1_w3379ab1b5c13c11b3_w3380ab1b5c13c11_w3381ab1b5c13_w3382ab1b5_w3383ab1\">\n<img alt=\"Struct A After Replacing Contents at Index\" aria-label=\"Open image in gallery mode\" class=\"image expandable\" data-fancy=\"gallery\" data-gallery=\"gallery\" data-remote=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb_replaceybyindex.png?_LANG=enus\" data-title=\"\" height=\"777\" role=\"button\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/structsaandb_replaceybyindex.png?_LANG=enus\" style=\"cursor: pointer;\" tabindex=\"0\" width=\"522\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__topic_d13002e1_d13003e1_d13004e1_d13005e1_d13006e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1059459e327\">\n                        \n Moving Structs\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8510e1_d8511e1_d8512e1\">Detach a Struct member from its parent, making it a top node. For example:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStruct-&gt;$parent = \"\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8513e1_d8514e1_d8515e1\">Move a Struct to another Struct. For example:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;$parent = vStructB</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18218e1_d18219e1_d18220e1\">This detaches the StructA from its current parent and adds it as a member to the specified StructB.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8516e1_d8517e1_d8518e1\">Moving a Struct member to a different position within the parent Struct:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;$index = 5</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__p_d18221e1_d18222e1_d18223e1\">This makes StructA the 5th member of its parent.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"fjy1665702564615__li_d8519e1_d8520e1_d8521e1\">Move a Struct member to the last position in its parent member list:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vStructA-&gt;$index = -1</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wdh1665702564728.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Example: Moving Structs</a><p>This example demonstrates how an existing Struct can be inserted as a member of another Struct.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cnk1665702564805.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Example: Removing Members</a><p>This example demonstrates how Struct members can be removed (detached) from their parent.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527544\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527544\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Adding, Copying, Moving, and Replacing Struct Members Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Adding, Copying, Moving, and Replacing Struct Members You can add and replace members in existing Structs, insert them at specified positions, detach them, or move them to new positions, or to new Structs. Assume that the variables vStructA and vStructB refer to the following Structs, respectively: Figure 1. StructA (Insects) and StructB (Fishes) Adding a Member to a Struct If a struct variable refers to an empty Struct, you can add a new member by specifying the new member name after the de-reference operator and assigning it a value. If the member does not yet exist, it is added. For example, to create Struct A, you can start with creating an empty Struct and adding a member: vStructA = $newstruct vStructA->a = \"ant\" Copy If a Struct has one member, you can append a named Struct member by specifying -1 as the index position. For example vStructA->a{-1} = \"aphid\" vStructB->a{-1} = \"angelfish\" Copy This implicitly inserts a new member named a after the last member named a , or as the last member if there was no a . Copying and Replacing Struct Members The following code copies members of Struct B to Struct A. vStructA->b = vStructB->c Copy Assignment is by value, so the existing values for the StructA members are replaced by the values specified in the right side of the assignment. If no other struct variables point to these members, they are deleted. The new values are inserted in at the point where the first b member was located. Figure 2. Struct A with New Values for Members named b Replacing and Appending Struct Members by Name and Index When using the Struct index operator after a member name, only the member at that index position is changed. Variables vStructA and vStructB refer to the original contents of the Structs illustrated in Figure 1 . The following code accesses the members of Struct 1 by both name and index and changes its contents. Explain this code vStructA->a{2} = vStructB->c [ 1 ] vStructA->b{-1} = vStructB->a [ 2 ] Copy Replaces the second member named a in StructA ( aphid ) with the values of the members named c in StructB ( catfish and clownfish ). Copies the values of members named a in StructB ( anglefish and anemonefish ) after the last member named b in StructA ( butterfly ). Figure 3. Struct A After Replacing Contents by Name and Index Copying and Replacing Struct Members by Index Only You can also add Struct members at a specific index position in the list of members using the wildcard to specify a collection and the index operator to specify a position in the collection (that is, the list of members). Variables vStructA and vStructB refer to the original contents of the Structs illustrated in Figure 1 . Explain this code vStructA->*{4} = vStructB->c [ 1 ] vStructA->*{-1} = vStructB->a{2} [ 2 ] Copy Replaces the fourth member in StructA ( butterfly ) with the values of the members named c in StructB ( catfish and clownfish ). Copies the values of second members named a from StructB ( anemonefish ) after the last member in StructA. Figure 4. Struct A After Replacing Contents at Index Moving Structs Detach a Struct member from its parent, making it a top node. For example: vStruct->$parent = \"\" Copy Move a Struct to another Struct. For example: vStructA->$parent = vStructB Copy This detaches the StructA from its current parent and adds it as a member to the specified StructB. Moving a Struct member to a different position within the parent Struct: vStructA->$index = 5 Copy This makes StructA the 5th member of its parent. Move a Struct member to the last position in its parent member list: vStructA->$index = -1 Copy Related Links Example: Moving Structs This example demonstrates how an existing Struct can be inserted as a member of another Struct. Example: Removing Members This example demonstrates how Struct members can be removed (detached) from their parent. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}